ubDate>Fri, 03 Feb 2023 22:08:21 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://wtong2017.github.io/projects/artmirror/</guid><description>Art Mirror is a VR soundstage for teachers and students to emulate cinematography lighting in virtual scenarios. Lighting education is a foundational component of cinematography education. However, many art schools do not have expensive soundstages for traditional cinematography lessons. Thus, migrating physical setups to virtual experiences is a potential solution driven by metaverse initiatives. This project is also presented in the poster session of IEEE VRW 2023.</description></item><item><title>Pvis2023datavideo</title><link>https://wtong2017.github.io/publications/pvis2023datavideo/</link><pubDate>Fri, 03 Feb 2023 21:55:35 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://wtong2017.github.io/publications/pvis2023datavideo/</guid><description/></item><item><title>AsymCollabVis</title><link>https://wtong2017.github.io/publications/asymcollabvis/</link><pubDate>Wed, 18 Jan 2023 23:08:48 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://wtong2017.github.io/publications/asymcollabvis/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Vrw2023artmirror</title><link>https://wtong2017.github.io/publications/vrw2023artmirror/</link><pubDate>Tue, 17 Jan 2023 21:46:03 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://wtong2017.github.io/publications/vrw2023artmirror/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Vr23CondAccept</title><link>https://wtong2017.github.io/news/vr2023/</link><pubDate>Thu, 12 Jan 2023 12:36:11 +0800</pubDate><guid>https://wtong2017.github.io/news/vr2023/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Vis2022conf</title><link>https://wtong2017.github.io/news/vis2022/</link><pubDate>Fri, 09 Dec 2022 00:49:17 +0900</pubDate><guid>https://wtong2017.github.io/news/vis2022/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Vtvisit</title><link>https://wtong2017.github.io/news/vtvisit/</link><pubDate>Fri, 09 Dec 2022 00:35:48 +0900</pubDate><guid>https://wtong2017.github.io/news/vtvisit/</guid><description/></item><item><title>